          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1679046408025-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>diced chicken breast</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> your<strong> garam masala</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>curry powder</strong> and<strong> half</strong> your <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add the <strong>marinated chicken </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray (or two!) and place in the oven for 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and starting to char – this is your <strong>tandoori chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1679046412786-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1679046412786-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1679046412786-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
