          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1679046417060-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1679046422761-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1679046422761-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1679046422761-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1679046422761-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1679046422761-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>remaining garam masala </strong>and <strong>remaining curry powder </strong>to the pan and cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened</p><p>Once thickened, remove the pan from the heat and stir through the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, <strong>tandoori chicken </strong>(reserve the tray[s]) and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped coriander </strong>– this is your <strong>butter chicken curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1679046428764-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
